<0><0>How are “Average” and “Spent Avera: <0><0>How are “Average” and “Spent Average MTD” calculated?</0></0><1>They are both the average cumulative spending by day for the three months before the selected “compare” month.</1>
<0><0>How is cash flow calculated?</0></: <0><0>How is cash flow calculated?</0></0><1>Cash flow shows the balance of your budgeted accounts over time, and the amount of expenses/income each day or month. Your budgeted accounts are considered to be “cash on hand,” so this gives you a picture of how available money fluctuates.</1>
<0><0>How is net worth calculated?</0></: <0><0>How is net worth calculated?</0></0><1>Net worth shows the balance of all accounts over time, including all of your investments. Your “net worth” is considered to be the amount you’d have if you sold all your assets and paid off as much debt as possible.
